  "text": "The human skin contains approximately one million T cells per cm 2 , which amounts to almost 20 billion T cells in total [CITATION_1] . This is nearly twice as many T cells as those circulating in the blood. T RM cells, like all memory T cells, can be distinguished from naïve T cells by expression of CD44, a marker of antigen experience.",
